                <note>
<p>WAIT</p>
<p>expectare denotes waiting for something, almost as a mere mental act, as a feeling, without practical reference or accessory meaning.</p>
<p>praestolari refers to waiting for something with the nuance that the person waiting intends, after the arrival of the object waited for, to do something.</p>
<p>opperiri is a poetic word for waiting.  </p>
<p>Note that the distinction between warten and harren is absent in Latin.</p>
